Shares of $AMCO skyrocketed over 60% Tuesday after announcing on Monday that its subsidiaries will benefit from the recent tariff changes by the China Government. 
The export tariff of 94 commodities well related to iron and steel industries will adjust from May 2015. 90 commodities will be exempt while the other 4 will see a tax reduction.
Armco Metals Holdings is a distributor of imported metal ores and a steel recycler in China.

status_message:
Shares of $CNDO gapped up 44% Thursday after releasing 2 company update announcements.
Coronado Biosciences, Inc. entered an exclusive license agreement with NeuPharma, Inc. to develop and commercialize, 3rd Generation EGFR inhibitors on a worldwide basis. Under the terms of the agreement, The company will pay NeuPharma an up-front licensing fee as well as development and sales-based milestone payments and will pay a tiered single digit royalty on net sales.
$CNDO also announced today the formation of a new company, Mustang Therapeutics, Inc. focusing on the preclinical and clinical development, as well as commercialization of proprietary Chimeric Antigen Receptor (CAR-T) technology. The deal is valued at $40 million for the development of these CAR-T cells via up-front and milestone payments to City of Hope, anticipating that the first two CAR-T cells will begin enrollment in human clinical trials at the City of Hope this year.

$AMRN rallied Thursday after the biopharmaceutical company, announced financial results for the quarter.
Amarin Corporation plc. focuses on the commercialization and development of therapeutics to improve cardiovascular health.
The company posted $16.5 million in net product revenue from Vascepa sales in Q4 2014 compared to $14.1 million in Q3 2014, an increase of 17%.
Vascepa (icosapent ethyl), is Amarin's first FDA approved product, a highly-pure, omega-3 fatty acid product available by prescription.
Amarin also reported $54.2 million in product revenue in 2014 as compared to $26.4 million in 2013, an increase of 105%.
About a week ago the company announced that it entered into a definitive securities agreement with institutional investors, including both existing and new investors, for the private placement of $52,822,618.50 of restricted American Depositary Shares, each representing one share of Amarin's Series A Convertible Preference Shares, par value 0.05 per share, in the capital of the Company.
